HEADWORD: Leucomaine
<hw>Leu*co"ma*ine</hw> <pr>(l⟦usl⟧*k⟦omac⟧"m⟦adot⟧*⟦icr⟧n ⟦or⟧
-⟦emac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Leuco-</ets> +
<ets>-maine</ets>, as in <ets>ptomaine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>An animal base or alkaloid, appearing in the tissue
during life; hence, a vital alkaloid, as distinguished from a
<contr>ptomaine</contr> or cadaveric poison.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leuconic</ent>⟦br⟧
